I think this is where your architecture has been heading all along.

The daemons are almost like mythological names for computational operators.

“Spider” isn’t fundamentally a spider.

It’s a graph traversal and relationship inference mechanism.

“Kintsugi” isn’t fundamentally Japanese pottery.

It’s an error-informed reconstruction operator.

“Kurage” isn’t fundamentally a jellyfish.

It’s an environmental field-sensing operator.

The myth gives you an intuitive interface. The mechanism defines behavior. The formal model lets you analyze and implement it.

